title: make check failed on old OS X versions
body:
`make check` failed on old OS X versions (Mountain Lion and Mavericks).

The errors look like:

```
..... SKIPED ....
'+sse2' is not a recognized feature for this target (ignoring feature)
'+sse2' is not a recognized feature for this target (ignoring feature)
'+sse2' is not a recognized feature for this target (ignoring feature)
error: could not copy "/private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.0.ll" to "/private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.ll": couldn't copy path (the source path is not an existing file; from="/private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.0.ll"; to="/private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.ll")
error: failed to remove /private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.0.ll: couldn't unlink path (no such file or directory (No such file or directory); path=/private/tmp/rust-TxJdrI/rustc-1.0.0-alpha.2/x86_64-apple-darwin/test/run-make/simd-ffi/simd.0.ll)
error: aborting due to 2 previous errors
```

Full compilation log for Mountain Lion https://gist.github.com/plashchynski/26b757cf77a7e9cc045a and for Mavericks https://gist.github.com/plashchynski/9a000165017141f7b29c
